  "text": "Mesenchymal stem (or stromal) cells (MSCs) are fibroblastlike, multipotent progenitor cells which can be isolated from bone marrow, umbilical cord, gingiva, fats, and other tissues [CITATION_1] . MSCs also have powerful immunomodulatory properties and can be considered as a potential tool for cell-based immunotherapy",
